reg_info.full_title: O. Reg. 585/06: SERVICES THAT CANNOT BE IDENTIFIED AS A SPECIAL SERVICE
reg_info.reg_name_text: SERVICES THAT CANNOT BE IDENTIFIED AS A SPECIAL SERVICE

content.section: Services that cannot be identified as a special service
content.content: 1. For the purposes of clause 326 (5) (a) of the Act, the following services are prescribed as services that cannot be identified as a special service under clause 326 (1) (a) of the Act: 1. Health programs and services under Part II of the Health Protection and Promotion Act. O. Reg. 585/06, s. 1.
content.raw_html:
1. For the purposes of clause 326 (5) (a) of the Act, the following services are prescribed as services that cannot be identified as a special service under clause 326 (1) (a) of the Act:

1. Health programs and services under Part II of the Health Protection and Promotion Act. O. Reg. 585/06, s. 1.
